14/12/2009
BELGRADE, Serbia -- The war crimes prosecutor's office has received letters containing death treats against President Boris Tadic, Rasim Ljajic, the head of Serbia's council for co-operation with The Hague tribunal, and war crimes prosecutor Vladimir Vukcevic, local media reported on Sunday (December 13th). The letters were sent from various locations in the United States. This has happened before, says Bruno Vekaric, spokesman for the war crimes prosecutor's office. He told B92 that similar threats have been received from the United States and from the Balkans, a total of 66 letters so far. (B92, Tanjug - 13/12/09)
